http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Thiruvananthapuram/13-recommended-for-Padma-awards/article13995253.ece

The State government has recommended 13 persons from Kerala for this year’s Padma awards.The names of persons representing different fields were announced here on Monday by Culture Minister K.C. Joseph who was the convener of the Cabinet sub-committee set up the government to prepare the list of persons for the awards.Gandhian P. Gopinathan Nair is the only name recommended for the Padmabhushan award this year.The list of personalities for the Padmasree awards includes V.P. Gangadharan and M.I. Sahadulla (medicine), Kathakali artiste Chemancheri Kunhiraman Nair, playback singer P. Jayachandran and lyricist and director Haripad Sreekumaran Thampi (Arts), Akkitham Achuthan Namboodiri (literature), P.U. Thomas (social service), Director, Satish Dhawan Space Centre, Sriharikota, P. Kunhikrishnan (science and technology), Preeja Sreedharan and Sunny Thomas (sports), Muraleedharan Kesavan (social work) and K.M. Roy (journalism).“The list was prepared by the search committee as per the guidelines and rules specified by the Central government. All the norms were adhered to and there has been no violation. The entire list was approved by the State Cabinet,” Mr. Joseph told reporters, adding that the list was being revealed in the light of media reports alleging irregularities in the selection process.The government, he said, was not aware of any guidelines issued by the Supreme Court.“We went by the norms specified by the Union Home Ministry and the relevant statute and rules.”